<p>George Will put out a piece <a href="http://www.philly.com/philly/opinion/20130303_Liberals_locked_in_the_past.html">in the Inky</a> this morning (Probably a few days after the same piece was put out elsewhere) and, right off the bat, made a statement I strongly disagreed with. He suggests that Social Security is obsolete because of greater life expectancy. No George, life expectancy may have improved for pundits like <em>you</em>, but they haven't changed much for people of modest means and/or for people with physically-demanding jobs.<br />
